The actions are supported by trade unions and a number of leftist public organizations.
In addition to raising the modest wages paid to ordinary Walmart and fast food workers, the protestors aim to create union organizations there.
So far, this sector of the economy is almost not covered by the trade union movement.
46 cents a year?
Promotions began last week, after Thanksgiving, on the so-called &quot;Black Friday&quot;, when America was hit by an orgy of giveaways, which captured millions of ordinary people and sometimes accompanied by scuffles.
On this day, some employees of the Walmart Corporation, which employs 2.2 million people around the world, left their jobs and picketed, along with trade unions and leftist activists, the stores of the corporation, whose goods are designed for people of modest and middle income.
Walmart sells everything from diapers, hunting rifles and car batteries to vacuum cleaners, eggs and milk.
Products in his stores are on average 8% to 27% cheaper than in large supermarkets.
Therefore, many low-paid Walmart employees shop only at their place of work.
The availability and range of products have made Walmart one of America&#39;s largest corporations.
Critics say Walmart can afford to sell it cheap, in part because it pays little to its employees.
The latter also complain about harsh working conditions, such as a shortage of forklift trucks or hand scanners.
Black Friday protesters demanded higher wages and complained that the cost of health insurance provided by the corporation had jumped from $ 30 to $ 100 a month.
The typical Walmart employee earning $ 9.5 an hour couldn&#39;t afford the expense, they said.
Scientists at the University of California, Berkeley argue that if Walmart raises the average salary to $ 12 an hour, it will cost the corporation $ 3.2 billion.
This is about 1.1% more than she spends on her salary now.
If Walmart shifts the entire pay rise onto the shoulders of customers, then each visit to the store will cost them only 46 cents more.
For the year they will spend some $ 12.39 more than they do now.
Walmart supporters are pleased to note that the protests took place in only nine states and did not cause the slightest damage to the corporation.
Black Friday ran in its stores from 8 pm Thursday to midnight the next day, during which time Walmart was selling about 5,000 items per second.
In total, its cash registers made nearly 100 million transactions on Black Friday.
Corporate spokesman Dan Fogelman argued in an interview with the left-wing Huffington Post that a total of &quot;fewer than five&quot; Walmart employees have left jobs and that the protest was just &quot;another PR stunt&quot; by the union that organized it.
&quot;Free cash register!&quot;
