What do you think about the end of the world in less than a month?
This is just one of the many unsettling news that we humans get caught up in so easily.
Together with The Tap Tap, we constantly joke about this topic and say that we are the only group in the world that can muster enough positive energy to delay or prevent the end of the world.
Moreover, in December you are going to give absolutely unique three concerts against the end of the world.
Could you tell the readers more about this?
This is a nationwide fundraising event that we have been planning for two years now.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential of the Mayan calendar, which was announced to end on December 21 at 11:10 am.
The day before this event, on December 20th at 21:00, three concerts will start in parallel in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end, roughly speaking, at the moment when the May calendar ends on the island of Kiribati in the Pacific Ocean, whose time zone is 12 hours earlier than ours.
Who came up with this idea?
Initially, it was my idea, then we came up with everything together with our artist Gonza Augusta.
In addition to the fact that we want to accumulate enough positive energy and prevent the end of the world, we also want to think together with the public about the state of this world we will one day pass on to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the May calendar, we have created a unique collection of items from shoes, T-shirts, bags and original keys against the end of the world. These things can be bought on the website www.e-tap.cz and thereby support us at the same time.
The Tap Tap, along with other musicians, also sang a anti-doomsday anthem called &quot;End of the World Canceled&quot;.
Will the already beloved YouTube anthem be played at these benefit concerts?
Of course, at the very end, if in the end everything works out and the end of the world does not come.
It will be sung by all performers at all concerts at the same time.
The hymns will also be played simultaneously live on Czech television.
The lyrics to this song were written and played the role of Jesus in the video by Tomasz Hanak, he also participates in the performance of Xindl X ...
How did you start working with them?
We also collaborate with other personalities of Czech cultural life, as we organize many charity events and concerts.
We are trying to actively involve them in these projects.
It turned out that many people like working with us, they are interested.
Where will the proceeds from the concert against the end of the world go?
For the purchase of equipment for the STUDEO barrier-free educational center, for the sixth year we have been working this way with the civic association Tap at the Jedlichki Institute.
