Some people come to us with a romantic performance and fly in the clouds, and when they find out that they have to go to rehearsals twice a week, attend preparatory courses and spend a lot of time on the road, they very quickly lose their enthusiasm.
But this happens in any group that wants to work and achieve something.
The Tap Tap currently has twenty members.
How many were there at the beginning in 1998?
Only one Lady Angelovich.
We are an open group, people come and go, it cannot be prevented.
For those who have desire and willpower, our doors are always open.
