Imitators only need to add a couple of letters to get the right to register their trademarks.
So from Gucci it turns out Lu-Gucci, instead of Prada, you can register Prada-Kny.
In the same way, German companies are legally copied, for example, the sports goods manufacturer Puma.
Pattloch opens a folder containing the records of the Beijing Trademark Office.
