The same applies to the total number of valid trademarks, only 5.5 million pieces.
In 2011, 1.8 billion yuan of fees were paid.
To put it simply, this means that each registration costs an average of RMB 1,280 or 160 euros.
It costs many times more to challenge it, as the case of the German family-owned company Freudenberg shows.
For more than seven years, the concern has been fighting against the Chinese plagiarist.
The Germans managed to ensure that their illegal production of counterfeit car parts was eliminated.
However, the imitator secured the Chinese rights to the Freudenberg trademark.
This was an oversight of its own, as surnames in Germany cannot be protected, says Hanno Wentzler, chairman of the board of Freudenberg Chemical Specialties in Munich.
