After the elections, there was an attempt to solve the problem with quotas and higher taxes for foreign workers.
Unexpected consequences
While the fall in fertility has a known impact on the nation&#39;s economic growth, tax revenues, medical spending, and immigration policy, the Singapore case is also starting to have some unexpected consequences.
The government is making efforts not to build so many small housing units.
