Inveterate basketball traveler Hector &quot;Hetin&quot; Reyes has been involved with the sport for over 60 years and has traveled all over the world thanks to him.
Few people in Puerto Rico have as many basketball stories as Hector “Hetin” Reyes.
And after all, before a cerebral hemorrhage confined him to a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes was immersed in the sport for over 60 years, as a small player, a Major League basketball player, commissioner and chief executive of BSN with the Bayamon Cowboys and president of the Basketball Federation. ...
