&quot;Basketball was my life.&quot;
Reyes is not exaggerating in making this statement.
The walls of his house, almost all adorned with photographs and memorabilia collected over his long journey, bear witness to this.
Bayamon in the heart
With his greatest emotions, he retains those that remember his journey through the Cowboys, from the mid-50s as a player until 1982, when he turned 15 years old as a co-agent or contract agent.
“Those were my best years and I enjoyed the most because I had the opportunity to be part of the eight Cowboys Championships since 1967, as an agent, co-agent or manager.
