And remember, bad is good for those with an apocalyptic mindset.
And he&#39;s not the only professor to offer doomsday courses in this theoretically last semester in history.
At Temple University, Associate Professor Barry Wacker teaches a course in Media, Culture and the End of the World.
Each week, students explore apocalyptic topics such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and bacteria, and global warming.
“We are analyzing why these ideas spread over time,” he said, and the way hypothetical scenarios are proposed that cause certain human actions.
If nuclear material falls into the hands of terrorists, for example, a war could break out.
This month, students analyzed films with apocalyptic themes and studied how they relate to real life examples.
“I tried to educate students about what is possible, probably, plausible, and impossible,” Wacker said.
