&quot;We&#39;re not adding &#39;2012&#39; to always be able to read the course again in case the world doesn&#39;t end,&quot; Restall said.
Despite the &quot;inevitable destruction&quot;, students must study, prepare projects, and take final exams.
At Penn State, the final exam will be taken on the eve of the Apocalypse, leaving students with no choice but to work &quot;until the very night that the world is supposed to end,&quot; Restall said.
The courses have proven to be quite popular.
