We received emails in the weeks leading up to the semester from people asking if there were more places.
Students, in turn, assure that this course is one of the most interesting.
“I love to see what people do to comfort themselves,” said Brigid Robinson, a 23-year-old religion and sociology student from Haddonfield, New Jersey, in Rutgers Camden.
And the apocalyptic way of thinking, secular or religious, is just a matter of comfort or lack thereof.
Will Vekesa, a 25-year-old psychology and nursing student, said he watched all the apocalyptic films.
